                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Permuting the order of the background traffic patterns during training did not deteriorate the performance during evaluation. In fact, evaluation runs exhibited lower variance, a better fastest transfer, and similar average transfer time compared to the experiments shown in 5a. Moreover, fewer experiments had to be aborted. These results suggest that MARLIN's robustness might be further improved by feeding data from diverse scenarios to the algorithm."
